25/04/2006
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The trial against six Bosnian Croats indicted for war crimes is scheduled to begin at the UN tribunal Wednesday (26 April).
The six -- Jadranko Prlic, Bruno Stojic, Slobodan Praljak, Milivoj Petkovic, Valentin Coric and Berislav Pusic -- were charged in March 2004 with involvement in ethnic cleansing during the period from 1992 to 1995.
In other news, the trial of a former Bosnian Croat military member, Nika Obradovic, charged with war crimes committed in BiH, opened at the Mostar Cantonal Court on Monday.
Prosecutors say his victims were Bosniak civilians in the BiH municipality of Stolac.
(Dnevni avaz, Vecernji list - 25/04/06;
ICTY Web site - 24/04/06)
